From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 06 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] usb: typec: tcpm: allow SRC_ATTACH_WAIT when external Vbus
 is present

When a self-powered UFP (e.g. a DP display/monitor that also sources 5V
on Vbus for charging) is connected at boot, the HUSB311 TCPC reports
VBUS_PRES=1 during tcpm_init().  This causes port->vbus_present=true and
port->vbus_vsafe0v=false.

Since Vbus remains stable at 5V (no transition), no POWER_STATUS
interrupt fires afterward, so vbus_vsafe0v is never recovered to true.
The SRC_ATTACH_WAIT state requires vbus_vsafe0v before scheduling
SRC_ATTACHED, so TCPM freezes indefinitely.

Fix: when entering SRC_UNATTACHED and our own Vbus regulator is not
active (vbus_source=false), mark vbus_vsafe0v=true.  External Vbus from
the UFP does not conflict with our source attachment — we can still
enable our own regulator to assert Vbus as source.  This matches the
USB Type-C spec intent: the DFP only needs Vbus at vSafe0V relative to
*its own* prior sourcing, not relative to external power.

Signed-off-by: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c b/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
--- a/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/tcpm.c
@@ -3944,6 +3944,15 @@ static void run_state_machine(struct tcpm_port *port)
 		if (!port->non_pd_role_swap)
 			tcpm_swap_complete(port, -ENOTCONN);
 		tcpm_src_detach(port);
+		/*
+		 * If our Vbus regulator is not active but the TCPC reports Vbus
+		 * present (e.g., a self-powered UFP such as a display/monitor is
+		 * sourcing Vbus), do not block source attachment.  External Vbus
+		 * does not prevent us from later enabling our own regulator, so
+		 * treat the current state as vSafe0V from our side.
+		 */
+		if (!port->vbus_source)
+			port->vbus_vsafe0v = true;
 		if (port->potential_contaminant) {
 			tcpm_set_state(port, CHECK_CONTAMINANT, 0);
 			break;
